<refsect1>
<title>Debugging GEGL</title>
<refsect2>
<para>
The best way to debug GEGL is to constantly run the unit tests while coding.
If you introduce new code, you should write new unit tests for these as well. 
</para>
</refsect2>

<refsect2>
<title>Environment variables</title>
<formalpara>
<title><envar>GEGL_LOG_ON</envar></title>
<para>
If this variable is set, GEGL will print out extensive debugging 
messages. These messages contain various file and line numbers
to help follow what is happening. The functions that are useful
for this gegl_log_debug, gegl_log_info, gegl_log_message, and gegl_log_direct, which 
which are defined <filename>gegl-utils.h</filename>. Grep the 
source to see how they are used. If you do not wish to see these any longer just unset the 
variable.
</para>
</formalpara>


</refsect2>

